      "text": "All 13 key requirements pass. Here's a summary of everything delivered:\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Deliverables Complete\n\n### Files Created\n| File | Size | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `query1.html` | 27 KB | Complete Three.js black hole visualization |\n| `screenshot.png` | 912 KB | Rendered screenshot (84.4% non-black, center brightness 171) |\n| `operation_sequence.json` | 6.3 KB | 11-step operation record |\n\n---\n\n### Implementation Highlights\n\n**Physics/Visual**\n- **Backward ray-tracing** via GLSL fragment shader with `#define MAX_STEPS 150` (constant, not uniform)\n- **Gravitational lensing**: geodesic bending `dir += -k·pos/r³·stepLen` at each march step\n- **Accretion disk**: y=0 plane, r∈[3,10], with temperature gradient (hot white-yellow → orange → dark red)\n- **Relativistic Doppler boost**: `(1/(1-β·cosθ))^4` — brighter left, darker right\n- **Photon ring glow** near r=2.5·r_s even for absorbed rays (prevents pure-black center)\n- **Procedural starfield**: two-scale 3D hash grid with blue supergiants, red dwarfs, twinkling `sin(iTime)`\n\n**Anti-Black-Screen Compliance** (all 13 checks pass)\n- `scene.add(mesh)` + `frustumCulled = false` ✓\n- `document.body.appendChild(renderer.domElement)` ✓\n- `renderer.getDrawingBufferSize()` + `Math.max(...,1)` guard ✓\n- `camera.getWorldDirection()` every frame ✓\n- Explicit `t_plane = -pos.y/dir.y` disk intersection (disk never missed on zoom-out) ✓\n- Absorbed rays output glow, never pure black ✓\n\n**UI**\n- Frosted-glass \"GARGANTUA\" card with gradient sci-fi font\n- `<input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"anim-toggle\" checked>` — fully visible, DOM-actionable\n- OrbitControls: left-click rotate, right-click pan, scroll zoom (distance 1.5–60)",
